Explanation
- The endpoint function dispatch_auths is defined in app/api/cms/admin.py with the route decorator:
  @admin_api.route("/permission/dispatch/batch", methods=["POST"])
  which explicitly allows POST.
- That admin_api Blueprint is registered under the cms Blueprint in app/api/cms/__init__.py with url_prefix="/admin".
- The cms Blueprint is registered on the application in app/__init__.py with url_prefix="/cms".
- Combining the prefixes yields the full path /cms/admin/permission/dispatch/batch.
- The code explicitly lists only methods=["POST"]. Per the instruction to base method acceptance on the code (not on framework runtime behavior or automatic handling), only POST is accepted; other HTTP methods (including HEAD and OPTIONS) are not listed and therefore considered not acceptable.
